# Full Strelok APK Data Extraction

## Phase 1: Install Required Tools

### 1.1 Install Java Runtime
```powershell
winget install Microsoft.OpenJDK.21 --accept-source-agreements --accept-package-agreements
```

### 1.2 Install jadx Decompiler
```powershell
winget install skylot.jadx --accept-source-agreements --accept-package-agreements
```

### 1.3 Install Python androguard
```powershell
pip install androguard
```

## Phase 2: Decompile classes.dex

### 2.1 Run jadx on classes.dex
Target: [strelok_extracted/classes.dex](BallisticsCalculator-iOS/strelok_extracted/classes.dex) (1.05 MB)

```powershell
jadx -d strelok_decompiled --show-bad-code strelok_extracted/classes.dex
```

Output: `strelok_decompiled/` folder with Java source files

### 2.2 Decode AndroidManifest.xml
```powershell
python -c "from androguard.core.axml import AXMLPrinter; print(AXMLPrinter(open('strelok_extracted/AndroidManifest.xml','rb').read()).get_xml())" > AndroidManifest_decoded.xml
```

### 2.3 Decode resources.arsc
```powershell
python -c "from androguard.core.resources import ARSCParser; arsc=ARSCParser(open('strelok_extracted/resources.arsc','rb').read()); print(arsc.get_strings_resources())"
```

## Phase 3: Extract Ballistics Data

### 3.1 Find Database Classes
```powershell
grep -rl "SQLiteDatabase\|SQLiteOpenHelper" strelok_decompiled/
```

### 3.2 Find Field Usage
```powershell
grep -rn "true_magnification\|same_atm\|target_type\|bullet_bc\|bullet_speed" strelok_decompiled/
```

### 3.3 Find Calculation Engine
```powershell
grep -rn "calculateTrajectory\|ballistic\|trajectory\|coriolis\|spin.*drift" strelok_decompiled/
```

### 3.4 Extract String Constants
```powershell
grep -rn "CREATE TABLE\|INSERT INTO\|SELECT.*FROM" strelok_decompiled/
```

## Phase 4: Present All Findings

### 4.1 Database Schema Usage
- Which fields are read/written
- Which fields are used in calculations vs UI only

### 4.2 Ballistics Engine
- Core calculation classes
- Formula implementations
- Physics constants

### 4.3 Data Structures
- Model classes (Rifle, Cartridge, etc.)
- Enums and constants

### 4.4 Verification
- Compare extracted schema with our current implementation
- Identify any missing fields or calculations

## Expected Output
- Full Java source tree in `strelok_decompiled/`
- Decoded XML manifest
- Comprehensive report of all ballistics-related code
- Field-by-field analysis showing actual usage
